    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="KT192-kilavi">piriviṭai vaṟpuṟutta vaṉpoṟaiyetir aḻintu kiḻatti uraittatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">Told by HER, desolate in the face of encouragement given to her in the time of separation.</p>
          </div>
          

        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="KT192">
<l>                īṅkē varuva riṉaiya lavareṉa</l>
<l>                vaḻāaṟkō viṉiyē nōynon tuṟaivi</l>
<l>                miṉṉiṉ ṟūvi yiruṅkuyil poṉṉi</l>
<l>                ṉuraitikaḻ kaṭṭaḷai kaṭuppa mācciṉai</l>
<l>                naṟuntātu koḻutum poḻutum</l>
<l>                varuṅkuraṟ kūnta ṟaivaru vēṉē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
     <l>“Here he will come, <note place="foot">Here for once is a clear example of an inserted imperative: <term xml:lang="ta">avar</term>, the subject to <term xml:lang="ta">varuvar</term>, is positioned only after the <term xml:lang="ta">iṉaiyal</term>. And still it would also be possible to read an pronominal noun with a complete pronominal ending: <term xml:lang="ta">iṉaiyalavar</term> "he, who doesn't know despair".</note> do not despair!”</l>
     <l>
        <choice>
            <seg>[How am] I not to cry now,</seg>
            <seg>Won't I cry now,</seg>
        </choice>
     </l>
     <l rend="indent3">o you who stay
        <choice>
            <seg>[beside me]</seg>
            <seg>with me</seg>
        </choice>
        in [my] pain?<note place="foot">Or another connection for line 1: "If I won't cry now, saying [to myself] '...', o you ...?"</note>
     </l>
     <l>I pull at [my] tresses with growing locks</l>
     <l rend="indent">all<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">poḻutum</term>: is <term xml:lang="ta">-um</term> an indefinite particle here?</note> the time when the dark Koel pecks</l>
     <l rend="indent">fragrant pollen from the mango twigs so that it resembles</l>
     <l rend="indent">a touch-stone, glittering with grated gold, [its] feathers flash-like.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
